# Google Calendar API
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/ → create or select a project
# 2. Enable "Google Calendar API"
# 3. Create an API key (Credentials → Create Credentials → API key)
#    Restrict it to "Google Calendar API" and your domain for production
# 4. Find your calendar ID in Google Calendar:
#    Settings → your calendar → "Calendar ID" (looks like xxx@group.calendar.google.com)
#    For a public calendar, set sharing to "Make available to public"

GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID=your-calendar-id@group.calendar.google.com
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-google-api-key

# ── Event metadata convention ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Add these lines at the TOP of any Google Calendar event description
# to control how it appears on the website:
#
#   Subsoc: PoetSoc           ← which sub-society hosted it
#   Image: https://...        ← event photo URL (or Google Drive share link)
#   Gallery: /gallery#slug    ← deep-link to gallery section (past events only)
#
# The rest of the description is shown as the event summary.
